        "content": "<p>Either put a - in front of your second proof (so, <code>proof -</code>), or end the proof one line earlier by replacing your <code>hence</code> with <code>thus</code> (what's happening is that <code>proof</code> without the <code>-</code> applies a default rule on your goal which here will be exI already, so it's been transformed to $F x \\lor G x$, and your <code>thus</code> complains that this can't be unified with the term you gave it)</p>",
